Functional beverages have gained significant popularity in recent years due to the growing health and wellness trend among consumers. The market can be segmented based on product type, distribution channel, and region. In terms of product type, functional beverages include a wide range of options such as functional juices, energy drinks, functional water, sports drinks, enhanced coffee and tea, dairy alternatives, and others. Each of these segments caters to different consumer preferences and needs. When it comes to distribution channels, functional beverages are commonly sold through supermarkets/hypermarkets, convenience stores, online retail platforms, and other channels. Finally, the market is segmented geographically into regions such as North America, Europe, Asia-Pacific, South America, and the Middle East and Africa, each presenting unique opportunities and challenges for market players.

